  "description": "The concentration in Sociology (leading to a Bachelor of Arts) provides a foundation in sociological theory and methods and the opportunity to cultivate more specialized knowledge in the discipline\u2019s substantive interests. Students develop that focus through their coursework, taking courses in diverse areas such as social inequality, family and gender, organizations, environmental sociology, race and ethnicity and globalization.\u00a0 Students refine their interests during the senior seminar and through their completion of a senior thesis or capstone project. Ten courses are\u00a0required to complete the concentration.",
